abilities.name: Damage Bind
abilities.text: Each Pokémon that has any damage counters on it (both yours and your opponent's) can't use any Poké-Powers.

attacks.name: Gigavolt
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage plus 30 more damage. If tails, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Reflect Energy
attacks.text: Move an Energy card attached to Ampharos to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

cards.name: Bulbasaur

attacks.name: Find a Friend
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Grass Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

cards.flavorText: A strange seed was planted on its back at birth. The plant sprouts and grows with this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Surprise Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

cards.name: Dratini

attacks.name: Wrap
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

cards.flavorText: It is called the "Mirage Pokémon" because so few have seen it. Its shed skin has been found.

cards.name: Weedle

attacks.name: Multiply
attacks.text: Search your deck for Weedle and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

cards.flavorText: Its poison stinger is very powerful. Its bright-colored body is intended to warn off its enemies.

abilities.name: Froth
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you play Azumarill from your hand to evolve 1 of your Active Pokémon, you may use this power. Each Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Water Punch
attacks.text: Flip a coin for each Water Energy attached to Azumarill. This attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage for each heads.

attacks.name: Thundershock
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Reflect Energy
attacks.text: If you have any Benched Pokémon and if there are any basic Energy cards attached to Ampharos, take 1 of those Energy cards and attach it to 1 of those Pokémon.

attacks.name: Bad News
attacks.text: If the number of cards in your opponent's hand is at least 6, choose a number of cards there, without looking, until your opponent has 5 cards left. Have your opponent discard the cards you chose.

attacks.name: Prize Count
attacks.text: If you have more Prize cards left than your opponent, this attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage.

cards.name: Aggron

attacks.name: Second Strike
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 40 damage plus 40 more damage.

attacks.name: Guard Claw
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to Aggron by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

cards.flavorText: You can tell its age by the length of its iron horns. It claims an entire mountain as its territory.

abilities.name: Reactive Protection
abilities.text: Any damage done to Aerodactyl by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon is reduced by 10 for each React Energy card attached to Aerodactyl (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Power Blow
attacks.text: Does 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy attached to Aerodactyl.

attacks.name: Speed Stroke
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects, including damage, done to Aerodactyl by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon-ex.

cards.name: Alakazam

abilities.name: Damage Swap
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may move 1 damage counter from 1 of your Pokémon to another as long as you don't Knock Out that Pokémon. This power can't be used if Alakazam is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Confuse Ray
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

cards.flavorText: Its brain can outperform a supercomputer. Its intelligence quotient is said to be 5000.

attacks.name: Feint Attack
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 20 damage to that Pokémon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, Poké-Powers, Poké-Bodies, or any other effects on that Pokémon.

attacks.name: Doom News
attacks.text: Return all Energy cards attached to Absol G to your hand. The Defending Pokémon is Knocked Out at the end of your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Giga Drain
attacks.text: Remove from Venusaur the number of damage counters equal to the damage you did to the Defending Pokémon.

cards.name: Arcanine
cards.flavorText: This legendary Chinese Pokémon is considered magnificent. Many people are enchanted by its grand mane.

cards.name: Ampharos

abilities.name: Jamming
abilities.text: After your opponent plays a Supporter card from his or her hand, put 1 damage counter on each of your opponent's Pokémon. You can't use more than 1 Jamming Poké-Body each turn.

attacks.name: Cluster Bolt
attacks.text: You may discard all Lightning Energy attached to Ampharos. If you do, this attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon that has any Energy cards attached to it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

cards.flavorText: The tip of its tail shines brightly. In the olden days, people sent signals using the tail's light.

cards.name: Beedrill δ
rules: This Pokémon is both Grass Metal type.

abilities.name: Final Sting
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may Knock Out Beedrill. If you do, choose 1 of your opponent's Defending Pokémon. That Pokémon is now Paralyzed and Poisoned. Put 2 damage counters instead of 1 on that Pokémon between turns. This power can't be used if Beedrill is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Super Slash
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is an Evolved Pokémon, this attack does 50 damage plus 30 more damage.

attacks.name: Phoenix Flame
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, shuffle Blaine's Moltres and all cards attached to it into your deck (after doing damage).

cards.name: Aerodactyl

abilities.name: Prehistoric Power
abilities.text: No more Evolution cards can be played. This power stops working while Aerodactyl is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

cards.flavorText: A ferocious prehistoric Pokémon that goes for the enemy's throat with its serrated saw-like fangs.

cards.name: Celebi & Venusaur-GX
rules: TAG TEAM rule: When your TAG TEAM is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 3 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Pollen Hazard
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned, Confused, and Poisoned.

attacks.name: Evergreen-GX
attacks.text: Heal all damage from this Pokémon. If this Pokémon has at least 1 extra Grass Energy attached to it (in addition to this attack's cost), shuffle all cards from your discard pile into your deck. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

cards.name: Caterpie

abilities.name: Adaptive Evolution
abilities.text: This Pokémon can evolve during your first turn or the turn you play it.

cards.flavorText: For protection, it releases a horrible stench from the antennae on its head to drive away enemies.

cards.name: Bastiodon

abilities.name: Protective Wall
abilities.text: Prevent all damage done to your Benched Pokémon by your opponent's attacks.

attacks.name: Anger Revenge
attacks.text: If Bastiodon was damaged by an attack during your opponent's last turn, this attack does 40 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

cards.flavorText: Any frontal attack is repulsed. It is a docile Pokémon that feeds on grass and berries.

cards.name: Altaria

attacks.name: Midnight Eyes
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Stadium Power
attacks.text: If there is any Stadium card in play, this attack does 40 damage plus 30 more damage.

cards.flavorText: It flies gracefully through the sky. Its melodic humming makes you feel like you're in a dream.

abilities.name: Extreme Speed
abilities.text: You pay Colorless less to retreat Arcanine for each Energy attached to it.

attacks.name: Fire Blow
attacks.text: You may discard any number of Fire Energy cards attached to Arcanine when you use this attack. If you do, flip a number of coins equal to the number of Fire Energy cards you discarded. This attack does 30 damage plus 30 more damage for each heads.

cards.name: Metapod

abilities.name: Adaptive Evolution
abilities.text: This Pokémon can evolve during your first turn or the turn you play it.

attacks.name: Harden
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokémon would be damaged by an attack, prevent that attack's damage done to this Pokémon if that damage is 60 or less.

cards.flavorText: A steel-hard shell protects its tender body. It quietly endures hardships while awaiting evolution.

abilities.name: Dig Well
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may look at the top 3 cards of your deck, choose as many Water Energy cards as you like, and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Discard the other cards. This power can't be used if Blastoise is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Aqua Press
attacks.text: Does 20 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy attached to all Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's).

attacks.name: Double Launcher
attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy attached to Blastoise. Choose 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. This attack does 60 damage to each of them. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) Blastoise can't use Double Launcher during your next turn.

cards.name: Blastoise

abilities.name: Rain Dance
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may attach 1 Water Energy card to 1 of your Water Pokémon. (This doesn't use up your 1 Energy card attachment for the turn.) This power can't be used if Blastoise is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Hydro Pump
attacks.text: Does 40 damage plus 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to Blastoise but not used to pay for this attack's Energy cost. You can't add more than 20 damage in this way.

cards.flavorText: A brutal Pokémon with pressurized water jets on its shell. They are used for high-speed tackles.

cards.name: Blastoise

abilities.name: Waterlog
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may attach as many basic Water Energy cards from your hand to any of your Pokémon in any way you like. If you do, your turn ends. This power can't be used if Blastoise is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Hydro Pump
attacks.text: Does 50 damage plus 20 more damage for each Water Energy attached to Blastoise but not used to pay for this attack's Energy cost. You can't add more than 40 damage in this way.

cards.flavorText: The jets of water it spouts from the rocket cannons on its shell can punch through thick steel.

cards.name: Articuno

attacks.name: Freeze Dry
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Blizzard
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. If tails, this attack does 10 damage to each of your own Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

cards.flavorText: A legendary bird Pokémon that is said to appear to doomed people who are lost in icy mountains.

attacks.name: Luring Flame
attacks.text: Switch the Defending Pokémon with 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. The new Defending Pokémon is now Burned.

attacks.name: Vapor Kick
attacks.text: If your opponent has any Water Pokémon in play, this attack does 30 damage plus 30 more damage.

cards.name: Lucario

attacks.name: Feint
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

attacks.name: Aura Sphere
attacks.text: Does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

cards.flavorText: It has the ability to sense the auras of all things. It understands human speech.

attacks.name: Dragon Dance
attacks.text: During your next turn, if any of your current Active Pokémon does damage to any Defending Pokémon, this attack does 40 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Dragon Song
attacks.text: Each Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

cards.name: Crobat δ
rules: This Pokémon is both Grass Metal type.

attacks.name: Radar Jam
attacks.text: Your opponent can't play any Trainer cards (except for Supporter cards) from his or her hand during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Target Attack
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 40 damage to that Pokémon. If that Pokémon already has damage counters on it, this attack does 60 damage instead. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

abilities.name: Bench Guard
abilities.text: As long as Brock's Rhydon is Benched, whenever 1 of your Benched Pokémon is damaged, you may do 10 of that damage to Brock's Rhydon instead. (If more than 1 of your Benched Pokémon is damaged at the same time, you may use this power once for each of them.)

attacks.name: Lariat
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

cards.name: Weedle

attacks.name: Tangle Drag
attacks.text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon.

cards.flavorText: Often found in forests and grasslands. It has a sharp, toxic barb of around two inches on top of its head.

attacks.name: Tropical Shake
attacks.text: This attack does 20 more damage for each type of basic Energy card in your discard pile. You can't add more than 100 damage in this way.

cards.name: Azumarill

attacks.name: Bubblebeam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

cards.flavorText: When it plays in water, it rolls up its elongated ears to prevent their insides from getting wet.

cards.name: Kakuna
cards.flavorText: While awaiting evolution, it hides from predators under leaves and in nooks of branches.

cards.name: Dark Ampharos
rules: This Pokémon is both Lightning Darkness type.

abilities.name: Darkest Impulse
abilities.text: As long as Dark Ampharos is in play, whenever your opponent plays an Evolution card from his or her hand to evolve 1 of his or her Pokémon, put 2 damage counters on that Pokémon. You can't use more than 1 Darkest Impulse Poké-Body each turn.

attacks.name: Shock Bolt
attacks.text: Discard all Lightning Energy attached to Dark Ampharos.

cards.name: Ludicolo

abilities.name: Table Service
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may heal 30 damage from 1 of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Punch and Run
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

cards.flavorText: If it hears festive music, all its muscles fill with energy. It can't help breaking out into a dance.

attacks.name: Heavy Blow
attacks.text: Does 70 damage minus 10 damage for each damage counter on Aggron. If Aggron has any React Energy cards attached to it, this attack does 70 damage instead.

attacks.name: Bound Crush
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 60 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) During your next turn, Aggron can't use Bound Crush.

cards.name: Tangela

attacks.name: Slam
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Mega Drain
attacks.text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

cards.flavorText: It tangles any moving thing with its vines. Their subtle shaking is ticklish if you get ensnared.

cards.name: Venusaur & Snivy-GX
rules: TAG TEAM rule: When your TAG TEAM is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 3 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Shining Vine
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, when you attach a Grass Energy card from your hand to it, you may switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Solar Plant-GX
attacks.text: This attack does 50 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. If this Pokémon has at least 2 extra Energy attached to it (in addition to this attack's cost), heal all damage from all of your Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

abilities.name: Safeguard
abilities.text: Prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Banette by your opponent's Pokémon-ex.

attacks.name: Night Murmurs
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is a Basic Pokémon, that Pokémon is now Confused.

cards.name: Venusaur V
rules: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Pollen Bomb
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep and Poisoned.

attacks.name: Solar Typhoon
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Solar Typhoon.

cards.name: Surskit

attacks.name: Sweet Scent
attacks.text: Heal 20 damage from 1 of your Pokémon.

cards.flavorText: It appears as if it is skating on water. It draws prey with a sweet scent from the tip of its head.

cards.name: Dialga

attacks.name: Time Bellow
attacks.text: Draw a card.

attacks.name: Flash Cannon
attacks.text: You may return all Energy cards attached to Dialga to your hand. If you do, remove the highest Stage Evolution card from the Defending Pokémon and shuffle that card into your opponent's deck.

cards.flavorText: It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.

cards.name: Caterpie
cards.flavorText: Perhaps because it would like to grow up quickly, it has a voracious appetite, eating a hundred leaves a day.

abilities.name: Blaze
abilities.text: As long as Blaziken's remaining HP is 40 or less, Blaziken does 40 more damage to the Defending Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Searing Flame
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Burned.

attacks.name: Damage Burn
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 50 damage plus 20 more damage.

cards.name: Ampharos

abilities.name: Jamming
abilities.text: After your opponent plays a Supporter card from his or her hand, put 1 damage counter on each of your opponent's Pokémon. You can't use more than 1 Jamming Poké-Body each turn.

attacks.name: Cluster Bolt
attacks.text: You may discard all Lightning Energy attached to Ampharos. If you do, this attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon that has any Energy cards attached to it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

cards.flavorText: The tip of its tail shines brightly. In the olden days, people sent signals using the tail's light.

attacks.name: Heat Tackle
attacks.text: Blaine's Arcanine does 10 damage to itself.

attacks.name: Firestorm
attacks.text: Discard 3 Fire Energy cards attached to Blaine's Arcanine in order to use this attack.

cards.name: Oddish

attacks.name: Trip Over
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

cards.flavorText: Its scientific name is "Oddium Wanderus." At night, it is said to walk nearly 1,000 feet on its two roots.

cards.name: Snivy
cards.flavorText: They photosynthesize by bathing their tails in sunlight. When they are not feeling well, their tails droop.

cards.name: Armaldo δ
rules: This Pokémon is both Fighting Metal type.

attacks.name: Delta Edge
attacks.text: If you have any Supporter cards in play, this attack's base damage is 20 instead of 70.

attacks.name: Fossil Charge
attacks.text: You may discard a Claw Fossil, Mysterious Fossil, Root Fossil, or Holon Fossil from your hand. If you do, choose 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon and do 30 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

cards.name: Caterpie

attacks.name: Surprise Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

cards.flavorText: When attacked by bird Pokémon, it resists by releasing a terrifically strong odor from its antennae, but it often becomes their prey.

cards.name: Caterpie

attacks.name: Nap
attacks.text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

cards.flavorText: When attacked by bird Pokémon, it resists by releasing a terrifically strong odor from its antennae, but it often becomes their prey.

cards.name: Clefable

attacks.name: Fairy Power
attacks.text: Return 1 of your Pokémon and all cards attached to it in your hand.

cards.flavorText: With its acute hearing, it can pick up sounds from far away. It usually hides in quiet places.

cards.name: Mew

attacks.name: Rainbow Wave
attacks.text: Choose a type of Energy other than Colorless attached to Mew. This attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon of that type (including Benched Pokémon). Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.

cards.flavorText: This Pokémon's body is covered by fine hairs that can be seen only under a microscope.

cards.name: Dratini

attacks.name: Hypnotic Gaze
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

cards.flavorText: It is called the "Mirage Pokémon" because so few have seen it. Its shed skin has been found.

cards.name: Masquerain

abilities.name: Tool Reversal
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may put a Pokémon Tool card attached to 1 of your Pokémon into your hand.

cards.flavorText: Its antennae have eye patterns on them. Its four wings enable it to hover and fly in any direction.

cards.name: Dark Crobat
rules: This Pokémon is both Grass Darkness type.

abilities.name: Black Beam
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Dark Crobat is your Active Pokémon, you may choose 1 of the Defending Pokémon. That Pokémon is now Poisoned. This power can't be used if Dark Crobat is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Dark Drain
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) Remove from Dark Crobat a number of damage counters equal to the number of your opponent's Pokémon in play.

attacks.name: Skill Dive
attacks.text: Does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

abilities.name: Pump Up
abilities.text: If your opponent has 3 or less Prize cards left, Drifblim FB gets +40 HP.

attacks.name: Shadow Ball
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. This attack does 40 damage to that Pokémon. Apply Weakness and Resistance.

cards.name: Clefable

attacks.name: Fairy Power
attacks.text: Return 1 of your Pokémon and all cards attached to it to your hand.

cards.flavorText: With its acute hearing, it can pick up sounds from far away. It usually hides in quiet places.

abilities.name: Gluey Slime
abilities.text: As long as Ariados is in play, each player must pay an additional Colorless to retreat his or her Active Pokémon. Gluey Slime can't make a player pay more than an additional Colorless to retreat a Pokémon, even if there is more than 1 Ariados in play.

attacks.name: Spider Force
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 damage plus 10 more damage. If tails, this attack does 20 damage and the defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

cards.name: Butterfree

attacks.name: Quiver Dance
attacks.text: Search your deck for a basic Energy card and attach it to this Pokémon. Shuffle your deck afterward. If you attached Energy in this way, heal 40 damage from this Pokémon.

cards.flavorText: It loves the honey of flowers and can locate flower patches that have even tiny amounts of pollen.

cards.name: Cradily δ
rules: This Pokémon is both Darkness Metal type.

attacks.name: Harsh Fluid
attacks.text: Put 5 damage counters on the Defending Pokémon at the end of your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Poison Tentacles
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

cards.name: Beedrill

attacks.name: Allergic Shock
attacks.text: During your next turn, if the Defending Pokémon is damaged by an attack, it is Knocked Out.

attacks.name: Twineedle
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads.

cards.flavorText: May appear in a swarm. Flies at violent speeds, all the while stabbing with the toxic stinger on its rear.

cards.name: Manaphy

attacks.name: Call for Family
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Aqua Ring
attacks.text: Switch Manaphy with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

cards.flavorText: Born on a cold seafloor, it will swim great distances to return to its birthplace.

cards.name: Ditto

abilities.name: Transform
abilities.text: If Ditto is your Active Pokémon, treat it as if it were the same card as the Defending Pokémon, including type, Hit Points, Weakness, and so on, except Ditto can't evolve, always has this Pokémon Power, and you may treat any Energy attached to Ditto as Energy of any type. Ditto isn't a copy of any other Pokémon while Ditto is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

cards.flavorText: Capable of copying an enemy's genetic code to instantly transform itself into a duplicate of the enemy.

cards.name: Chansey

attacks.name: Scrunch
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to Chansey during your opponent's next turn. (Any other effects of attacks still happen.)

attacks.name: Double-edge
attacks.text: Chansey does 80 damage to itself.

cards.flavorText: A rare and elusive Pokémon that is said to bring happiness to those who manage to catch it.

attacks.name: Devolution Wave
attacks.text: Count the number of React Energy cards attached to Cradily and choose up to that number of your opponent's Evolved Pokémon. Remove the highest Stage Evolution card from each of those Pokémon, then have your opponent shuffle those cards into his or her deck.

attacks.name: Linear Attack
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 30 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

cards.name: Pidgeot

attacks.name: Supersonic Flight
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

cards.flavorText: This Pokémon searches for food while flying at Mach 2. Its large claws make fearsome weapons.

cards.name: Celebi

attacks.name: Future Sight
attacks.text: Look at the top 5 cards of either player's deck and put them back on top of that player's deck in any order.

attacks.name: Leaf Bind
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

cards.flavorText: This Pokémon wanders across time. Grass and trees flourish in the forests in which it has appeared.

abilities.name: Form Change
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for another Deoxys and switch it with Deoxys. (Any cards attached to Deoxys, damage counters, Special Conditions, and effects on it are now on the new Pokémon.) If you do, put Deoxys on top of your deck. Shuffle your deck afterward. You can't use more than 1 Form Change Poké-Power each turn.

attacks.name: Swift

abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may remove 1 damage counter from each of your Pokémon. This power can't be used if Bellossom is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Dance 'til Dawn
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads. Bellossom is now Asleep.

cards.flavorText: Bellossom gather at times and seem to dance. They say that the dance is a ritual to summon the sun.

attacks.name: Stomp
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 20 more damage.

attacks.name: Fire Spin
attacks.text: Discard 2 Basic Energy cards attached to Entei or this attack does nothing.

cards.name: Pansage

attacks.name: Collect
attacks.text: Draw a card.

cards.flavorText: This Pokémon dwells deep in the forest. Eating a leaf from its head whisks weariness away as if by magic.

cards.name: Scyther

attacks.name: Twin Play
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Scyther and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Agility
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon during your opponent's next turn.

cards.flavorText: While young, they live together deep in the mountains, training themselves in how to fight with their scythes and move at high speeds.

cards.name: Snivy

attacks.name: Slam
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

cards.flavorText: It is very intelligent and calm. Being exposed to lots of sunlight makes its movements swifter.

cards.name: Octillery

attacks.name: Switch Cannon
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 30 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) Switch Octillery with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Ink Bomb
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing.

cards.flavorText: It traps foes with the suction cups on its tentacles, then smashes them with its rock-hard head.

cards.name: Blaziken

abilities.name: Firestarter
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may attach a Fire Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Fire Stream
attacks.text: Discard a Fire Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

cards.flavorText: When facing a tough foe, it looses flames from its wrists. Its powerful legs let it jump clear over buildings.

cards.name: Ho-Oh

abilities.name: Phoenix Turn
abilities.text: Once during your opponent's turn, if Ho-Oh would be Knocked Out by damage from an attack, you may flip a coin. If heads, Ho-Oh isn't discarded. Instead, remove all damage counter, Special Conditions, and other effects from Ho-Oh. Then, discard all cards attached to Ho-Oh (except for Energy cards). This counts as Ho-Oh being Knocked Out and your opponent takes a Prize card.

attacks.name: Rainbow Wing
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage time the number of different types of basic Energy cards attached to Ho-Oh.

cards.flavorText: Its feathers are in seven colors. It is said that anyone seeing it is promised eternal happiness.

attacks.name: Volt Tackle
attacks.text: Pikachu does 10 damage to itself.

abilities.name: Beating Wings
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Pidgeot is your Active Pokémon, you may shuffle 1 of your Benched Pokémon and all cards attached to it into your deck. This power can't be used if Pidgeot is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Sharp Beak
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 plus 30 more damage.

pokemons.name: bulbasaur
pokemons.quote:
A strange seed was
planted on its
back at birth. The plant sprouts
and grows with
this POKéMON.

pokemons.name: ivysaur
pokemons.quote:
When the bulb on
its back grows
large, it appears to lose the
ability to stand
on its hind legs.

pokemons.name: venusaur
pokemons.quote:
The plant blooms
when it is
absorbing solar energy. It stays
on the move to
seek sunlight.

pokemons.name: charmander
pokemons.quote:
Obviously prefers
hot places. When
it rains, steam is said to spout
from the tip of
its tail.

pokemons.name: charmeleon
pokemons.quote:
When it swings
its burning tail,
it elevates the temperature to
unbearably high
levels.

pokemons.name: charizard
pokemons.quote:
Spits fire that
is hot enough to
melt boulders. Known to cause
forest fires
unintentionally.

pokemons.name: squirtle
pokemons.quote:
Shoots water at
prey while in the
water. Withdraws into
its shell when in
danger.

pokemons.name: wartortle
pokemons.quote:
When tapped, this
POKéMON will pull
in its head, but its tail will
still stick out a
little bit.

pokemons.name: blastoise
pokemons.quote:
It deliberately
makes itself heavy
so it can with­ stand the recoil
of the water jets
it fires.

pokemons.name: caterpie
pokemons.quote:
It releases a stench from its red
antenna to repel enemies. It
grows by molting repeatedly.

pokemons.name: metapod
pokemons.quote:
This POKéMON is
vulnerable to
attack while its shell is soft,
exposing its weak
and tender body.

pokemons.name: butterfree
pokemons.quote:
In battle, it
flaps its wings
at high speed to release highly
toxic dust into
the air.

pokemons.name: weedle
pokemons.quote:
Often found in
forests, eating
leaves. It has a sharp
venomous stinger
on its head.

pokemons.name: kakuna
pokemons.quote:
Almost incapable
of moving, this
POKéMON can only harden its shell
to protect itself
from predators.

pokemons.name: beedrill
pokemons.quote:
Flies at high
speed and attacks
using its large venomous stingers
on its forelegs
and tail.

pokemons.name: pidgey
pokemons.quote:
A common sight in
forests and woods.
It flaps its wings at ground
level to kick up
blinding sand.

pokemons.name: pidgeotto
pokemons.quote:
Very protective
of its sprawling
territorial area, this POKéMON will
fiercely peck at
any intruder.

pokemons.name: pidgeot
pokemons.quote:
When hunting, it
skims the surface
of water at high speed to pick off
unwary prey such
as MAGIKARP.

pokemons.name: rattata
pokemons.quote:
Bites anything
when it attacks.
Small and very quick, it is a
common sight in
many places.

pokemons.name: raticate
pokemons.quote:
It uses its whis­
kers to maintain
its balance. It apparently
slows down if
they are cut off.

pokemons.name: spearow
pokemons.quote:
Il est incapable de voler à haute altitude.
Il se déplace très vite pour protéger
son territoire.

pokemons.name: fearow
pokemons.quote:
With its huge and
magnificent wings,
it can keep aloft without ever
having to land
for rest.

pokemons.name: ekans
pokemons.quote:
Moves silently
and stealthily.
Eats the eggs of birds, such as
PIDGEY and
SPEAROW, whole.

pokemons.name: arbok
pokemons.quote:
It is rumored that
the ferocious
warning markings on its belly
differ from area
to area.

pokemons.name: pikachu
pokemons.quote:
最近發表了聚集大量皮卡丘
來建造發電廠的計畫。

pokemons.name: raichu
pokemons.quote:
Its tail discharges electricity into
the ground, protecting it from
getting shocked.

pokemons.name: sandshrew
pokemons.quote:
Burrows deep
underground in
arid locations far from water.
It only emerges
to hunt for food.

pokemons.name: sandslash
pokemons.quote:
Curls up into a
spiny ball when
threatened. It can roll while
curled up to
attack or escape.

pokemons.name: nidoran-f
pokemons.quote:
Although small,
its venomous
barbs render this POKéMON dangerous.
The female has
smaller horns.

pokemons.name: nidorina
pokemons.quote:
The female's horn
develops slowly.
Prefers physical attacks such as
clawing and
biting.

pokemons.name: nidoqueen
pokemons.quote:
Its hard scales
provide strong
protection. It uses its hefty
bulk to execute
powerful moves.

pokemons.name: nidoran-m
pokemons.quote:
Saca las orejas por encima de la hierba para explorar
el territorio. Le protege su cuerno venenoso.

pokemons.name: nidorino
pokemons.quote:
An aggressive
POKéMON that is
quick to attack. The horn on its
head secretes a
powerful venom.

pokemons.name: nidoking
pokemons.quote:
One swing of its mighty tail can
snap a telephone pole as if it were
a matchstick.

pokemons.name: clefairy
pokemons.quote:
Its magical and
cute appeal has
many admirers. It is rare and
found only in
certain areas.

pokemons.name: clefable
pokemons.quote:
A timid fairy
POKéMON that is
rarely seen. It will run and hide
the moment it
senses people.

pokemons.name: vulpix
pokemons.quote:
At the time of
birth, it has
just one tail. The tail splits
from its tip as
it grows older.

pokemons.name: ninetales
pokemons.quote:
Very smart and
very vengeful.
Grabbing one of its many tails
could result in a
1000-year curse.

pokemons.name: jigglypuff
pokemons.quote:
When its huge eyes
light up, it sings
a mysteriously soothing melody
that lulls its
enemies to sleep.

pokemons.name: wigglytuff
pokemons.quote:
The body is soft
and rubbery. When
angered, it will suck in air and
inflate itself to
an enormous size.

pokemons.name: zubat
pokemons.quote:
Forms colonies in
perpetually dark
places. Uses ultrasonic waves
to identify and
approach targets.

pokemons.name: golbat
pokemons.quote:
Once it strikes,
it will not stop
draining energy from the victim
even if it gets
too heavy to fly.

pokemons.name: oddish
pokemons.quote:
During the day,
it keeps its face
buried in the ground. At night,
it wanders around
sowing its seeds.

pokemons.name: gloom
pokemons.quote:
It secretes a
sticky, drool-like
honey. Although sweet, it smells
too repulsive to
get very close.

pokemons.name: vileplume
pokemons.quote:
It has the world's
largest petals.
With every step, the petals shake
out heavy clouds
of toxic pollen.

pokemons.name: paras
pokemons.quote:
Burrows to suck
tree roots. The
mushrooms on its back grow by draw­
ing nutrients from
the bug host.

pokemons.name: parasect
pokemons.quote:
A host-parasite
pair in which the
parasite mushroom has taken over the
host bug. Prefers
damp places.

pokemons.name: venonat
pokemons.quote:
Lives in the
shadows of tall
trees where it eats insects. It
is attracted by
light at night.

pokemons.name: venomoth
pokemons.quote:
The dust-like
scales covering
its wings are color coded to
indicate the kinds
of poison it has.

pokemons.name: diglett
pokemons.quote:
Lives about one
yard underground
where it feeds on plant roots. It
sometimes appears
above ground.

pokemons.name: dugtrio
pokemons.quote:
A team of DIGLETT
triplets.
It triggers huge earthquakes by
burrowing 60 miles
underground.

pokemons.name: meowth
pokemons.quote:
Es de naturaleza nocturna. Le atraen los objetos
brillantes.

pokemons.name: persian
pokemons.quote:
Although its fur
has many admirers,
it is tough to raise as a pet
because of its
fickle meanness.

pokemons.name: psyduck
pokemons.quote:
While lulling its
enemies with its
vacant look, this wily POKéMON will
use psychokinetic
powers.

pokemons.name: golduck
pokemons.quote:
Often seen swim­
ming elegantly by
lake shores. It is often mistaken
for the Japanese
monster, Kappa.

pokemons.name: mankey
pokemons.quote:
Extremely quick to
anger. It could
be docile one moment then
thrashing away
the next instant.

pokemons.name: primeape
pokemons.quote:
Always furious
and tenacious to
boot. It will not abandon chasing
its quarry until
it is caught.

pokemons.name: growlithe
pokemons.quote:
Very protective
of its territory.
It will bark and bite to repel
intruders from
its space.

pokemons.name: arcanine
pokemons.quote:
A POKéMON that
has been admired
since the past for its beauty.
It runs agilely
as if on wings.

pokemons.name: poliwag
pokemons.quote:
Its newly grown
legs prevent it
from running. It appears to prefer
swimming than
trying to stand.

pokemons.name: poliwhirl
pokemons.quote:
Capable of living
in or out of
water. When out of water, it
sweats to keep
its body slimy.

pokemons.name: poliwrath
pokemons.quote:
An adept swimmer
at both the front
crawl and breast stroke. Easily
overtakes the best
human swimmers.

pokemons.name: abra
pokemons.quote:
Dieses Pokémon schläft 18 Stunden am Tag.
Bei Gefahr teleportiert es sich in Sicherheit,
ohne dabei aufzuwachen.

pokemons.name: kadabra
pokemons.quote:
It emits special
alpha waves from
its body that induce headaches
just by being
close by.

pokemons.name: alakazam
pokemons.quote:
Its brain can out­
perform a super­
computer. Its intelligence
quotient is said
to be 5,000.

pokemons.name: machop
pokemons.quote:
Loves to build
its muscles.
It trains in all styles of martial
arts to become
even stronger.

pokemons.name: machoke
pokemons.quote:
Its muscular body
is so powerful, it
must wear a power save belt to be
able to regulate
its motions.

pokemons.name: machamp
pokemons.quote:
Using its heavy
muscles, it throws
powerful punches that can send the
victim clear over
the horizon.

pokemons.name: bellsprout
pokemons.quote:
Even though its body is extremely
skinny, it is blindingly fast
when catching its prey.

pokemons.name: weepinbell
pokemons.quote:
Escupe Polvo Veneno para envenenar al enemigo y,
luego, lo liquida con Ácido.

pokemons.name: victreebel
pokemons.quote:
Said to live in
huge colonies
deep in jungles, although no one
has ever returned
from there.

pokemons.name: tentacool
pokemons.quote:
Son corps est principalement composé d’eau.
Ses yeux cristallins projettent d’étranges rayons.

pokemons.name: tentacruel
pokemons.quote:
80개의 촉수를 자유롭게
움직인다. 찔리면 독이 퍼져
극심한 고통을 겪게 된다.

pokemons.name: geodude
pokemons.quote:
Found in fields
and mountains.
Mistaking them for boulders,
people often step
or trip on them.

pokemons.name: graveler
pokemons.quote:
Rolls down slopes
to move. It rolls
over any obstacle without slowing
or changing its
direction.

pokemons.name: golem
pokemons.quote:
Its boulder-like
body is extremely
hard. It can easily withstand
dynamite blasts
without damage.

pokemons.name: ponyta
pokemons.quote:
Its hooves are 10
times harder than
diamonds. It can trample anything
completely flat
in little time.

pokemons.name: rapidash
pokemons.quote:
Very competitive,
this POKéMON will
chase anything that moves fast
in the hopes of
racing it.

pokemons.name: slowpoke
pokemons.quote:
Incredibly slow
and dopey. It
takes 5 seconds for it to feel
pain when under
attack.

pokemons.name: slowbro
pokemons.quote:
The SHELLDER that
is latched onto
SLOWPOKE's tail is said to feed
on the host's left
over scraps.

pokemons.name: magnemite
pokemons.quote:
Uses anti-gravity
to stay suspended.
Appears without warning and uses
THUNDER WAVE and
similar moves.

pokemons.name: magneton
pokemons.quote:
Formed by several
MAGNEMITEs linked
together. They frequently appear
when sunspots
flare up.

pokemons.name: farfetchd
pokemons.quote:
The sprig of
green onions it
holds is its weapon. It is
used much like a
metal sword.

pokemons.name: doduo
pokemons.quote:
A bird that makes
up for its poor
flying with its fast foot speed.
Leaves giant
footprints.

pokemons.name: dodrio
pokemons.quote:
Uses its three
brains to execute
complex plans. While two heads
sleep, one head
stays awake.

pokemons.name: seel
pokemons.quote:
The protruding
horn on its head
is very hard. It is used for
bashing through
thick ice.

pokemons.name: dewgong
pokemons.quote:
Stores thermal
energy in its
body. Swims at a steady 8 knots
even in intensely
cold waters.

pokemons.name: grimer
pokemons.quote:
Appears in filthy
areas. Thrives by
sucking up polluted sludge
that is pumped
out of factories.

pokemons.name: muk
pokemons.quote:
Thickly covered
with a filthy,
vile sludge. It is so toxic, even
its footprints
contain poison.

pokemons.name: shellder
pokemons.quote:
Its hard shell
repels any kind
of attack. It is vulnerable
only when its
shell is open.

pokemons.name: cloyster
pokemons.quote:
CLOYSTER that live
in seas with harsh
tidal currents grow large, sharp
spikes on their
shells.

pokemons.name: gastly
pokemons.quote:
Almost invisible,
this gaseous
POKéMON cloaks the target and
puts it to sleep
without notice.

pokemons.name: haunter
pokemons.quote:
Because of its
ability to slip
through block walls, it is said
to be from an­
other dimension.

pokemons.name: gengar
pokemons.quote:
Under a full moon,
this POKéMON
likes to mimic the shadows of
people and laugh
at their fright.

pokemons.name: onix
pokemons.quote:
As it grows, the
stone portions of
its body harden to become similar
to a diamond, but
colored black.

pokemons.name: drowzee
pokemons.quote:
Puts enemies to
sleep then eats
their dreams. Occasionally gets
sick from eating
bad dreams.

pokemons.name: hypno
pokemons.quote:
When it locks eyes
with an enemy, it
will use a mix of PSI moves such as
HYPNOSIS and
CONFUSION.

pokemons.name: krabby
pokemons.quote:
Its pincers are
not only powerful
weapons, they are used for balance
when walking
sideways.

pokemons.name: kingler
pokemons.quote:
The large pincer
has 10000 hp of
crushing power. However, its huge
size makes it
unwieldy to use.

pokemons.name: voltorb
pokemons.quote:
Usually found in
power plants.
Easily mistaken for a POKé BALL,
they have zapped
many people.

pokemons.name: electrode
pokemons.quote:
It stores electric
energy under very
high pressure. It often explodes
with little or no
provocation.

pokemons.name: exeggcute
pokemons.quote:
Often mistaken
for eggs.
When disturbed, they quickly
gather and attack
in swarms.

pokemons.name: exeggutor
pokemons.quote:
Legend has it that
on rare occasions,
one of its heads will drop off and
continue on as an
EXEGGCUTE.

pokemons.name: cubone
pokemons.quote:
死に別れた　母親の　骨を
頭に　覆っている。寂しいとき
大声で　泣くという。

pokemons.name: marowak
pokemons.quote:
骨に　灯った　呪いの　炎は
いつまでも　治らない　痛みを
体と　心に　残すという。

pokemons.name: hitmonlee
pokemons.quote:
When in a hurry,
its legs lengthen
progressively. It runs smoothly
with extra long,
loping strides.

pokemons.name: hitmonchan
pokemons.quote:
While apparently
doing nothing, it
fires punches in lightning fast
volleys that are
impossible to see.

pokemons.name: lickitung
pokemons.quote:
Its tongue can be
extended like a
chameleon's. It leaves a tingling
sensation when it
licks enemies.

pokemons.name: koffing
pokemons.quote:
Because it stores
several kinds of
toxic gases in its body, it is
prone to exploding
without warning.

pokemons.name: weezing
pokemons.quote:
Where two kinds
of poison gases
meet, 2 KOFFINGs can fuse into a
WEEZING over many
years.

pokemons.name: rhyhorn
pokemons.quote:
Its massive bones
are 1000 times
harder than human bones. It can
easily knock a
trailer flying.

pokemons.name: rhydon
pokemons.quote:
Protected by an
armor-like hide,
it is capable of living in molten
lava of 3,600
degrees.

pokemons.name: chansey
pokemons.quote:
A rare and elusive
POKéMON that is
said to bring happiness to those
who manage to get
it.

pokemons.name: tangela
pokemons.quote:
The whole body is
swathed with wide
vines that are similar to sea­
weed. Its vines
shake as it walks.

pokemons.name: kangaskhan
pokemons.quote:
The infant rarely
ventures out of
its mother's protective pouch
until it is 3
years old.

pokemons.name: horsea
pokemons.quote:
Hace su nido entre los corales. Si se siente en peligro,
escupe tinta y huye.

pokemons.name: seadra
pokemons.quote:
Capable of swim­
ming backwards by
rapidly flapping its wing-like
pectoral fins and
stout tail.

pokemons.name: goldeen
pokemons.quote:
せびれ　むなびれ　おびれが
ゆうがに　たなびくので
みずのおどりこ　とよばれる。

pokemons.name: seaking
pokemons.quote:
In the autumn
spawning season,
they can be seen swimming power­
fully up rivers
and creeks.

pokemons.name: staryu
pokemons.quote:
An enigmatic
POKéMON that can
effortlessly regenerate any
appendage it
loses in battle.

pokemons.name: starmie
pokemons.quote:
Its central core
glows with the
seven colors of the rainbow. Some
people value the
core as a gem.

pokemons.name: mr-mime
pokemons.quote:
If interrupted
while it is
miming, it will slap around the
offender with its
broad hands.

pokemons.name: scyther
pokemons.quote:
With ninja-like
agility and speed,
it can create the illusion that
there is more
than one.

pokemons.name: jynx
pokemons.quote:
Its cries sound like human speech.
However, it is impossible to tell
what it is trying to say.

pokemons.name: electabuzz
pokemons.quote:
Normally found
near power plants,
they can wander away and cause
major blackouts
in cities.

pokemons.name: magmar
pokemons.quote:
Its body always
burns with an
orange glow that enables it to
hide perfectly
among flames.

pokemons.name: pinsir
pokemons.quote:
If it fails to
crush the victim
in its pincers, it will swing it
around and toss
it hard.

pokemons.name: tauros
pokemons.quote:
When it targets
an enemy, it
charges furiously while whipping its
body with its
long tails.

pokemons.name: magikarp
pokemons.quote:
In the distant
past, it was
somewhat stronger than the horribly
weak descendants
that exist today.

pokemons.name: gyarados
pokemons.quote:
Rarely seen in
the wild. Huge
and vicious, it is capable of
destroying entire
cities in a rage.

pokemons.name: lapras
pokemons.quote:
A POKéMON that
has been over­
hunted almost to extinction. It
can ferry people
across the water.

pokemons.name: ditto
pokemons.quote:
It can freely recombine its own cellular structure to
transform into other life-forms.

pokemons.name: eevee
pokemons.quote:
Its genetic code
is irregular.
It may mutate if it is exposed to
radiation from
element STONEs.

pokemons.name: vaporeon
pokemons.quote:
수중에서의 생활에 적합한
몸으로 진화했다.
물에 녹으면 보이지 않게 된다.

pokemons.name: jolteon
pokemons.quote:
It accumulates
negative ions in
the atmosphere to blast out 10000-
volt lightning
bolts.

pokemons.name: flareon
pokemons.quote:
When storing
thermal energy in
its body, its temperature could
soar to over 1600
degrees.

pokemons.name: porygon
pokemons.quote:
A POKéMON that
consists entirely
of programming code. Capable of
moving freely in
cyberspace.

pokemons.name: omanyte
pokemons.quote:
Although long
extinct, in rare
cases, it can be genetically
resurrected from
fossils.

pokemons.name: omastar
pokemons.quote:
Apparently, it
cracked SHELLDER's
shell with its sharp fangs and
sucked out the
insides.

pokemons.name: kabuto
pokemons.quote:
A POKéMON that
was resurrected
from a fossil found in what was
once the ocean
floor eons ago.

pokemons.name: kabutops
pokemons.quote:
Its sleek shape is
perfect for swim­
ming. It slashes prey with its
claws and drains
the body fluids.

pokemons.name: aerodactyl
pokemons.quote:
A ferocious, pre­
historic POKéMON
that goes for the enemy's throat
with its serrated
saw-like fangs.

pokemons.name: snorlax
pokemons.quote:
Very lazy. Just
eats and sleeps.
As its rotund bulk builds, it
becomes steadily
more slothful.

pokemons.name: articuno
pokemons.quote:
A legendary bird
POKéMON that is
said to appear to doomed people who
are lost in icy
mountains.

pokemons.name: zapdos
pokemons.quote:
A legendary bird
POKéMON that is
said to appear from clouds while
dropping enormous
lightning bolts.

pokemons.name: moltres
pokemons.quote:
It is said to be the legendary bird Pokémon of fire.
Every flap of its wings creates a dazzling flare
of flames.

pokemons.name: dratini
pokemons.quote:
Long considered a
mythical POKéMON
until recently when a small
colony was found
living underwater.

pokemons.name: dragonair
pokemons.quote:
A mystical POKéMON
that exudes a
gentle aura. Has the ability
to change climate
conditions.

pokemons.name: dragonite
pokemons.quote:
An extremely
rarely seen
marine POKéMON. Its intelligence
is said to match
that of humans.

pokemons.name: mewtwo
pokemons.quote:
It was created by
a scientist after
years of horrific gene splicing and
DNA engineering
experiments.

pokemons.name: mew
pokemons.quote:
So rare that it
is still said to
be a mirage by many experts. Only
a few people have
seen it worldwide.

pokemons.name: chikorita
pokemons.quote:
A sweet aroma
gently wafts from
the leaf on its head. It is docile
and loves to soak
up the sun's rays.

pokemons.name: bayleef
pokemons.quote:
Die Knospen an seinem Hals geben ein
würziges Aroma ab, das andere aufheitert.

pokemons.name: meganium
pokemons.quote:
The aroma that
rises from its
petals contains a substance that
calms aggressive
feelings.

pokemons.name: cyndaquil
pokemons.quote:
It is timid, and
always curls it­
self up in a ball. If attacked, it
flares up its back
for protection.

pokemons.name: quilava
pokemons.quote:
Be careful if it
turns its back
during battle. It means that it will
attack with the
fire on its back.

pokemons.name: typhlosion
pokemons.quote:
If its rage peaks,
it becomes so hot
that anything that touches it will
instantly go
up in flames.

pokemons.name: totodile
pokemons.quote:
Its well-developed
jaws are powerful
and capable of crushing anything.
Even its trainer
must be careful.

pokemons.name: croconaw
pokemons.quote:
If it loses a
fang, a new one
grows back in its place. There are
always 48 fangs
lining its mouth.

pokemons.name: feraligatr
pokemons.quote:
When it bites with
its massive and
powerful jaws, it shakes its head
and savagely tears
its victim up.

pokemons.name: sentret
pokemons.quote:
A very cautious
POKéMON, it raises
itself up using its tail to get a
better view of its
surroundings.

pokemons.name: furret
pokemons.quote:
The mother puts its offspring to
sleep by curling up around them.
It corners foes with speed.

pokemons.name: hoothoot
pokemons.quote:
It always stands on one foot.
It changes feet so fast,
the movement can rarely be seen.

pokemons.name: noctowl
pokemons.quote:
Its eyes are
specially adapted.
They concentrate even faint light
and enable it to
see in the dark.

pokemons.name: ledyba
pokemons.quote:
It is very timid.
It will be afraid
to move if it is alone. But it will
be active if it is
in a group.

pokemons.name: ledian
pokemons.quote:
When the stars
flicker in the
night sky, it flutters about,
scattering a
glowing powder.

pokemons.name: spinarak
pokemons.quote:
It lies still in
the same pose for
days in its web, waiting for its
unsuspecting prey
to wander close.

pokemons.name: ariados
pokemons.quote:
It spins string
not only from its
rear but also from its mouth. It is
hard to tell which
end is which.

pokemons.name: crobat
pokemons.quote:
It flies so si­
lently through the
dark on its four wings that it may
not be noticed
even when nearby.

pokemons.name: chinchou
pokemons.quote:
It shoots positive
and negative elec­
tricity between the tips of its
two antennae and
zaps its enemies.

pokemons.name: lanturn
pokemons.quote:
The light it emits
is so bright that
it can illuminate the sea's surface
from a depth of
over three miles.

pokemons.name: pichu
pokemons.quote:
It is not yet
skilled at storing
electricity. It may send out a
jolt if amused
or startled.

pokemons.name: cleffa
pokemons.quote:
Si dice che sia facile incontrarlo dove sono
precipitate delle stelle cadenti.

pokemons.name: igglybuff
pokemons.quote:
It has a very soft
body. If it starts
to roll, it will bounce all over
and be impossible
to stop.

pokemons.name: togepi
pokemons.quote:
The shell seems to
be filled with
joy. It is said that it will share
good luck when
treated kindly.

pokemons.name: togetic
pokemons.quote:
They say that it
will appear before
kindhearted, car­ ing people and
shower them with
happiness.

pokemons.name: natu
pokemons.quote:
Because its wings
aren't yet fully
grown, it has to hop to get around.
It is always star­
ing at something.

pokemons.name: xatu
pokemons.quote:
They say that it
stays still and
quiet because it is seeing both the
past and future at
the same time.

pokemons.name: mareep
pokemons.quote:
If static elec­
tricity builds in
its body, its fleece doubles in
volume. Touching
it will shock you.

pokemons.name: flaaffy
pokemons.quote:
As a result of
storing too much
electricity, it developed patches
where even downy
wool won't grow.

pokemons.name: ampharos
pokemons.quote:
The tail's tip
shines brightly
and can be seen from far away. It
acts as a beacon
for lost people.

pokemons.name: bellossom
pokemons.quote:
BELLOSSOM gather
at times and
appear to dance. They say that the
dance is a ritual
to summon the sun.

pokemons.name: marill
pokemons.quote:
The tip of its
tail, which con­
tains oil that is lighter than wa­
ter, lets it swim
without drowning.

pokemons.name: azumarill
pokemons.quote:
会制作填满空气的泡泡。
当露力丽在河里玩的时候，
它就会用这个泡泡包住露力丽。

pokemons.name: sudowoodo
pokemons.quote:
Although it always
pretends to be a
tree, its composi­ tion appears to be
closer to a rock
than a plant.

pokemons.name: politoed
pokemons.quote:
울음소리가 울려 퍼지면
여기저기에서 발챙이와
슈륙챙이들이 모인다.

pokemons.name: hoppip
pokemons.quote:
To keep from being
blown away by the
wind, they gather in clusters. They
do enjoy gentle
breezes, though.

pokemons.name: skiploom
pokemons.quote:
The bloom on top
of its head opens
and closes as the temperature fluc­
tuates up and
down.

pokemons.name: jumpluff
pokemons.quote:
Once it catches
the wind, it deft­
ly controls its cotton-puff spores
to float, even
around the world.

pokemons.name: aipom
pokemons.quote:
Its tail is so
powerful that it
can use it to grab a tree branch and
hold itself up in
the air.

pokemons.name: sunkern
pokemons.quote:
It may drop out of
the sky suddenly.
If attacked by a SPEAROW, it will
violently shake
its leaves.

pokemons.name: sunflora
pokemons.quote:
태양 에너지에서 영양을 만들어낸다.
기온이 높은 낮에는 활발하게 움직이고
태양이 지면 뚝 하니 움직이지 않게 된다.

pokemons.name: yanma
pokemons.quote:
If it flaps its
wings really fast,
it can generate shock waves that
will shatter win­
dows in the area.

pokemons.name: wooper
pokemons.quote:
This POKéMON lives
in cold water. It
will leave the water to search
for food when it
gets cold outside.

pokemons.name: quagsire
pokemons.quote:
This carefree
POKéMON has an
easy-going nature. While swimming, it
always bumps into
boat hulls.

pokemons.name: espeon
pokemons.quote:
It uses the fine
hair that covers
its body to sense air currents and
predict its ene­
my's actions.

pokemons.name: umbreon
pokemons.quote:
When agitated,
this POKéMON pro­
tects itself by spraying poisonous
sweat from its
pores.

pokemons.name: murkrow
pokemons.quote:
Feared and loathed
by many, it is
believed to bring misfortune to all
those who see it
at night.

pokemons.name: slowking
pokemons.quote:
It has incredible
intellect and in­
tuition. Whatever the situation, it
remains calm and
collected.

pokemons.name: misdreavus
pokemons.quote:
It likes playing
mischievous tricks
such as screaming and wailing to
startle people at
night.
